<br>
As far as it goes the Hibs on my server Igraine were gettin quite uppity. There was a time when we had DF for weeks! Incursions by Hibs were real RP making opportunities! Life was great!<br>
<br>
Then the darkness came; Our best zerg leader fell beneath a pall (wife had a baby) and dissapeared from the sight of fair Camelot. At that same time Tretchery! Some of our Mightiest Knights (Our top alliance) were charmed by an evil Hibernian sorcerer (they left and all went to Hib to create a new guild). In desperation we all withdrew to seek consul with the wise (we called a truce with Hibernia to give them time to develop). <br>
<br>
It wasnt long however (dam-it wasnt long at all!) before foul Hibernians stormed our lands slaying all before them. They stole our most the most sacred Staff of Mighty Merlin! They aided (by keeping us busy elsewhere) the oafish lumbering giants of the North (Mids) to capture Excalibers Scabbard! All seemed lost. Dark were the days in fair Camelot then.<br>
<br>
But lo, a plan was laid to recapture all that was rightfully ours. The giants of the North could be ignored, being too dim of wit to be an urgent problem. The foul Hibernians must be dealt with, taught a lesson to instill fear in their childrens children. <br>
<br>
And so it was, in the darkest of days of the year and the darkest of hours of the night (Hibs go to bed early, they need their beauty sleep...<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) that we stole upon deep Hibernia slaying all who stood before us (we surprised em) conquering every stronghold in Hibernia (all keeps - old school tactics) to finally reach our goal and steal in upon their sanctuary most foul (relic keep). There, we took all, to punish the lowly Hibernians for ever daring to cast their dark gaze upon fair Camelot. <br>
<br>
and the Mightiest of the Mighty who led this great enterprise was none other than the greatest of men, previously vilified by braggarts as one who cared only for profit (Mercenary), but beneath such shallow view lies the heart of a true Warrior! The savior of us all! Let his name forever be spoken with the Greatest of Heros.<br>
<br>
<br>
Yep, yep, yep, since takin all the pwr relics the Hibs are definately nerfed. We had to call out the guards a few times shortly after that as Hibs seem to live for pwr, but now the Hib problem is much more manageable. Mids? ya they love the STR relics, but no wants to go after them, because the last time anyone had 6 relics youll never sleep!<br>
<br>
Casters rule RvR, make no mistake about it and if Mythic really wants to &quot;slow&quot; down and &quot;improve&quot; RvR battles it will have to improve certain Melee classes (Mercs/ BM's) and nerf casters.<br>
<br>
Oh well, back to whinning on the Merc board...GL all...<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nirala>Nirala</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>M.C. Hammah</span><br>  Posts: 360<br> <font color=#000000>(4/16/03 7:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=101.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We NERFED all uppity Hibs!!! MWHAAHAHAHA!!!!</span><hr size=1> Hah hah, sounds a lot like what happened on our server.  We albs got in a bit of a funk and didn't have any relics for a month or two, then we took all 3 power relics from the Hibs.  They tried a few times that first week to take them back, and after being soundly rebuffed (which, after beatin' on a relic keep for 10-15 minutes having an equal or greater amount show up to defend it is generally considered a sound rebuffing), they just kinda gave up.  Not sure if they're gonna snap out of it or not, from what I've heard a lot of them jumped servers or left for ShadowBane.  I've got my cleric perma-logged there just in case though <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Nirala HammahMastah<br>
