I honestly think its best when the relics change hands often. Not every night, but every few weeks. I think it helps keep all three realms alive. If a realm goes on several relic raids and gets defeated soundly every time, they'll get discouraged and will stop playing. But if a relic changes hands every few weeks, it'll keep everything lively. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Raeloran Twinblade</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, 50 Blademaster, Legendary Grandmaster Armorcrafter, Pellinor</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grayswandir@lighttanksofdaoc>Grayswandir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#000000>(4/17/03 11:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=101.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> and so...</span><hr size=1> Hey Nirala.<br>
<br>
I totally agree Raeloran - the relics do need to &quot;shared&quot; around for the well being of all realms. Somtimes I notice a certain boredom start to creep into ppl once they reach 50. Oh they tear up emain for awhile (or try), but after a few weeks of endless repetition, the start to lose some interest.<br>
<br>
The DR's and other events help but you can only do so much of that, so they make other chars which keeps em busy for awhile but not forever.<br>
<br>
Talking of Relics there is also IMO an imbalance issue OR seems to be. No realm seems to benefit as much drom the PWR relics as the Hibs. When they have them they are lethal. Even RvR against them is no fun - first to fire wins.<br>
<br>
Oh well, I am very interested to see what Mythic comes up with to &quot;improve&quot; (slow down) the RvR experience as they plan. I really cant see them do it if they dont nerf casters, at least in RvR. We could finally have some real melee battles, who knows?<br>
<br>
The RR just before the successful one I mentioned above was amazing; over 200 Albs and 200 Hib full armies in emain, we chased each or played cat and mouse all day. When we fianally met? I'd never seen so many paeople it was so awesome just see each other, we both stopped to look a minute - then we clashed, and honestly it was over in seconds (hibs had 3 pwr relics) - we lost and badly. <br>
<br>
We had sooooo many bodies stacked in Bolg (summoner) that people were wishing for an AOE rez...<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I suppose the Middies ae more dangerous with Str relics too, but our casters take care of that easy enough. Hibs with pwr relics are too dangerous.<br>
<br>
I suppose you might say that all melee classes get ripped a bit, being outclassed by our caster friends.<br>
<br>
Oh well, time to go before some zerker decides to explore my nether regions with his left axe...<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/embarassed.gif ALT=":o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
